The laundry detergent market can be segmented based on product type, application, and distribution channel. In terms of product type, the market offers powder detergent, liquid detergent, and detergent tablets. Powder detergent has been a traditional favorite due to its cost-effectiveness and ability to clean tough stains. Liquid detergents are gaining popularity due to their convenience and effectiveness on different types of fabrics. Detergent tablets are a convenient alternative for consumers seeking pre-measured doses for laundry. Regarding applications, laundry detergents cater to both household and commercial needs. Household detergents are the most commonly used, while commercial detergents serve a broader spectrum of industries such as hotels, laundromats, and hospitals. When it comes to distribution channels, laundry detergents are predominantly sold through supermarkets/hypermarkets, convenience stores, and online retail platforms. Supermarkets cater to the everyday shopping needs of consumers, convenience stores offer quick access to detergents, and online retail provides the convenience of purchasing from home.

